ed any dichotomous (data that can be divided into two categories) measure in cases where we were unable to analyse the data as ordinal data: 'good' Engel Class Outcome (classes I and II) versus 'bad' Engel Class Outcome (classes III and IV).    International League Against Epilepsy (ILAE) epilepsy surgery outcome (Wiser 2001).    Proportion of participants that experienced at least one adverse event from any source.   Proportion of participants that experienced each separate adverse event from any source.   Quality of life outcomes measured with validated scales.    An ITT approach was taken with all outcomes."}
